    "where R is the set of all reference embeddings, and H-mean is the harmonic mean.",
    "Score can be utilized in both reference-free and referencebased evaluation settings, making it one of the most widely used metrics for image captioning assessment.",
    "EMScore Similarly, EMScore (Shi et al., 2022) is a video captioning metric on both coarse-and fine-grained level.",
    "where the coarse-grained embedding matching c assesses the overall alignment between the entire video V and the caption X, and the fine-grained embedding matching f evaluates the alignment at a more detailed level by comparing individual frames of the video with specific words or phrases in the caption.",
    "Vision Transformer and Vanilla Transformer are used as video encoder and text encoder."
